PITUITARY

pituitary is the citizen who receives commands from hypothalamus and translates them into hormone releases that travel through the bloodstream to distant glands
this is the master gland of the endocrine system: anterior pituitary releases growth hormone, ACTH, TSH, prolactin, FSH, LH; posterior pituitary releases oxytocin and vasopressin
without pituitary, the brain's regulatory commands could not reach the adrenals, thyroid, or any other downstream gland

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe gland_ipc.zc
observe pituitary_gland.rana
observe hypothalamus.rana
observe adrenal_cortex.rana
observe thyroid.rana

the 7 properties of pituitary:
1 ENERGY zero point seven
2 PHASE zero point three
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point nine

VERB receive_releasing_factor
accept hormone-releasing factors from hypothalamus
each releasing factor is a specific molecular signal that triggers a specific pituitary hormone release

VERB release_hormone
emit the appropriate hormone into chemistry_field
the hormone propagates through bloodstream to its target gland

a master gland is not a controller
the pituitary executes orders from hypothalamus; it does not originate them
this is the substrate's hierarchy: brain decides, pituitary translates, downstream glands act
